study_pop.textblock:
        Patients with a clinical syndrome due to disease of a progressive nature, which leads to
        disturbances in multiple higher cortical functions, including memory, thinking,
        orientation, comprehension, calculation, learning capacity, language and judgment;

          1. Older adults with advanced dementia;

          2. Critically ill/unconscious patients;

          3. Patients at the end of life stage.

          4. Ventilated patients.
